<a href="https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/current/reference/html/data-access.html#transaction-declarative-annotations">Using
  @Transactional</a>:
In proxy mode (which is the default), only external method calls coming in through the proxy are intercepted.
This means that self-invocation (in effect, a method within the target object calling another method of the target object) does not lead to an actual
transaction at runtime even if the invoked method is marked with @Transactional.
